   "source": [
    "## Statistical Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Now that dispersions and LFCs were fitted, we may proceed with statistical tests to compute p-values and adjusted p-values for differential expresion. This is the role of the DeseqStats class. It has two mandatory arguments:\n",
    "\n",
    "dds, which should be a fitted DeseqDataSet object,\n",
    "\n",
    "contrast, which is a list of three strings of the form [\"variable\", \"tested_level\", \"control_level\"], or directly a contrast vector."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "id": "3cf325ae-7d14-4cc5-a42c-58e2c3bc1550",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ds = DeseqStats(\n",
    "    dds,\n",
    "    contrast=[\"condition\", \"Cancer\", \"Infection\"],\n",
    "    inference=inference\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "id": "b1bd405b-3491-4220-8476-741acbba34c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<pydeseq2.ds.DeseqStats at 0x2588714efe0>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 39,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ds"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2107e2fe-3bac-421b-b785-bf43a4643044",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "log2FoldChange > 0: genes upregulated in fibrosis relative to normal\n",
    "\n",
    "log2FoldChange < 0: genes downregulated in fibrosis (i.e., up in normal)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f3d6aeb6-ea35-49a5-b7f5-aa252073ad8b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "It also has a set of optional keyword arguments (see the API documentation), among which:\n",
    "\n",
    "alpha: the p-value and adjusted p-value significance threshold (0.05 by default),\n",
    "\n",
    "cooks_filter: whether to filter p-values based on cooks outliers (True by default),\n",
    "\n",
    "independent_filter: whether to perform independent filtering to correct p-value trends (True by default).\n",
    "\n",
    "In the section on multifactor analysis, we will also see how to use the contrast argument to specify according to which variable samples should be compared.\n",
    "\n",
    "Wald test\n",
    "PyDESeq2 computes p-values using Wald tests. This can be done using the summary() method, which runs the whole statistical analysis, cooks filtering and multiple testing adjustement included."
   ]
  },
