    "### Interpretation\n",
    "SMTN (smoothelin — smooth muscle cytoskeletal protein), NAPSA (napsin A — a canonical lung adenocarcinoma marker), LYN (a Src-family kinase involved in BCR signaling), and TUBB3 (beta-tubulin — cytoskeletal/neuronal) are your top discriminators. NAPSA being the second most important gene and appearing prominently upregulated in the volcano is particularly strong — it's a well-validated lung adenocarcinoma marker used clinically. LYN being high-importance and downregulated connects directly back to the CD22-mediated BCR regulation and BCR signaling pathways in your downregulated Reactome results. That's a mechanistically coherent loop: LYN suppression → impaired BCR signaling → the B-cell pathway suppression."
