    "## Annotation of the differentially expressed genes using ReactomePA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8416ea63-62ea-4a9a-a797-afc3a7de0ae0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Reactome is a curated database of human biological pathways. When you feed it a list of DEGs, it tells you:\n",
    "\n",
    "Which pathways are enriched\n",
    "How genes cluster into biological processes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ff25636f-bc1d-40e4-b4ec-e4ce3e377784",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "sigs is the dataframe that contains the differentially expressed gene list\n",
    "\n",
    "Next the gene IDs are extracted and if they are up regulated vs down regulated. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 137,
   "id": "bf7e5468-7bc0-4d5d-b8f2-f335df63fc04",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#pulls out the gene IDs\n",
    "deg_genes = sigs.index.tolist()\n",
    "#pulls out the up vs down regulated\n",
    "up_genes = sigs[sigs['log2FoldChange'] > 0].index.tolist()\n",
    "down_genes = sigs[sigs['log2FoldChange'] < 0].index.tolist()"
   ]
  },
  {
