  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "08c1b4dc-bb81-486d-ae73-d1dd1999b697",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Down Regulation Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Top pathways:\n",
    "Antigen Activates B Cell Receptor Leading CD22‑mediated BCR regulation\n",
    "Immunoregulatory interactions between lymphoid and non‑lymphoid cells\n",
    "\n",
    "##### Key downregulated genes:\n",
    "\n",
    "LYN (critical BCR kinase)\n",
    "CD19 (B‑cell co‑receptor)\n",
    "CD22 (BCR inhibitory receptor)\n",
    "DAPP1, PIK3AP1 (downstream BCR signaling adaptors)\n",
    "\n",
    "##### Interpretation\n",
    "This is a textbook signature of reduced B‑cell activation and suppressed adaptive immune signaling.\n",
    "When CD19, LYN, and CD22 all drop together, it usually means the B‑cell receptor signaling machinery is broadly suppressed, leading to reduced antigen responsiveness, impaired B‑cell activation, and a shift toward an immunologically inactive or tolerogenic state"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2097f541-7c66-4d43-8f30-d0dc4235fbf5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Up‑Regulation Interpretation\n",
    "##### Top pathways:\n",
    "Signal Transduction  \n",
    "Signaling by Receptor Tyrosine Kinases (RTKs)  \n",
    "Syndecan Interactions / Laminin & ECM Interactions  \n",
    "Chemokine Receptors Bind Chemokines  \n",
    "Extracellular Matrix Organization\n",
    "\n",
    "##### Key upregulated genes:\n",
    "GRB7, IRS1 — central adaptors for RTK signaling (EGFR, ERBB, IGF1R)\n",
    "ITGA2, ITGA3, ITGB4, SDC1, HSPG2, THBS1 — integrins and ECM‑binding molecules\n",
    "CCL2, CCL13, CCL17, CXCL5, CXCR3 — chemokines and chemokine receptors\n",
    "MMP7, MMP19 — matrix metalloproteinases involved in ECM remodeling\n",
    "AREG — EGFR ligand promoting growth and epithelial activation\n",
    "FGFBP2 — enhancer of FGF signaling\n",
