    "# Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "This analysis presents an end to end differential gene expression workflow applied to bronchoalveolar lavage fluid (BALF) RNA sequencing data from GSE252118, a prospective study examining host transcriptional responses in lung cancer and pulmonary infection. Using PyDESeq2, 512 significant genes (padj < 0.05, |log2FC| > 0.5) were identified from 402 samples (279 infection and 123 cancer) and carried forward for downstream analysis. Dimensionality reduction with PCA and UMAP revealed clear condition‑level separation in log1p‑normalized expression space, supported by hierarchical clustering and volcano plot visualization. A Random Forest classifier trained on the significant gene set, optimized through grid‑search hyperparameter tuning and evaluated with permutation‑based feature importance, demonstrated that host gene expression alone contains discriminative signal for separating cancer from infection.\n",
